  {
    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "> This PR means that when you are using searchFunction, we will do a shallow clone of the helper at each keystroke (or search). Not a deep clone.\r\n\r\n@vvo Got thrown by this as I was trying to use `AlgoliaSearchHelper` and they don't exist. Docs just say `options.searchFunction`'s...[\"with the helper as a parameter\"](https://community.algolia.com/instantsearch.js/documentation/#initialization)\r\n\r\nAt any rate, if I want to call `AlgoliaSearchHelper` methods from within `searchFunction` (e.g. `.on`, `.setPage`), what's the best way to do this?",
    "created_at": "2017-01-12T18:21:02Z",
    "html_url": "https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch/pull/873#issuecomment-272240425",
    "id": 272240425,
    "issue_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/algolia/instantsearch/issues/873",
    "node_id": "MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDI3MjI0MDQyNQ==",
